Bluzer's Rock Band Series For Phase Shift *12/06/14*

by bluzer » Mon Apr 30, 2012 9:37 pm

To bulk download(the jDLC containers) use Jdownloader 2 beta!


.......

Q: Whats Phase Shift?

A: If you don't know, then you shouldn't be in this thread...If you want to know. GO HERE => Phase Shift

Q: Can I play these with FoF/FoFiX?

A: NO! These are made specifically for => Phase Shift..........BUT(read answer b)!

B: Yes...with some alteration to the audio files you can play these in FoF/iX.

Load all tracks in Audacity

1) Combine all drum tracks together
2) Make Bass guitar a stereo pair.
3) Change Project Rate to 44100Hz(bottom left corner)
4) ALL tracks need to be stereo & 44100Hz audio or FoF/iX will play them to fast/slow.
5) Combine vocals.ogg & song.ogg together for FoFiX's song.ogg(include drums/vocals/song in a song.ogg for FoF/GH3, only if your doing this for FoF or GH3 PC)
6) Export drums combined = drums.ogg, guitar = guitar.ogg, bass guitar(stereo) = rhythm.ogg, vocals & extras = song.ogg, choose your ogg quality.
7) ....Enjoy!

.......

For now, just the main setlist songs will be posted.

I will make JDownloader DLC files for each setlist for people who want to DL all links with out doing DLing 1by1....soon.

I'll probably migrate my RB3 thread links(PS links) here in the future. I re-did them...rb3 is here now. xD

  • Full audio support(proper split audio)
  • Upgraded RB3 PRO drum charts(where available)
  • Exact preview times(2013; now song.ini related)
  • Volume's adjusted according to the songs.dta
  • All difficulties filled in, supported & not supported(song.ini)
  • PRO mode(where available, mainly a few DLC)
